Package org.neo4j.kernel.api.query

Class WaitingOnLockEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.api.query.ExecutingQueryStatus
      • org.neo4j.kernel.api.query.WaitingOnLock
        • org.neo4j.kernel.api.query.WaitingOnLockEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, LockWaitEvent
    class WaitingOnLockEvent
extends WaitingOnLock
implements LockWaitEvent
    This is both a status state in the state machine of ExecutingQuery, and a LockWaitEvent. The reason for this is to avoid unnecessary object allocation and indirection, since there is always a one-to-one mapping between the status corresponding to the lock we are waiting on (caused by LockTracer.waitForLock(LockType, ResourceType, long, long...) the event of waiting on a lock}) and the event object used to signal the end of the wait.
